How to integrate payment Gateway
To implement Flutterwave payments in a Spring Boot application,
you generally follow a flow where the backend initializes the transaction,
the frontend collects payment, and the backend verifies the status
1)Choose a payment gateway(Flutterwave)
2)Register on the platform and optain API keys
3)Add dependencies in your pom.xml
4)Configure API keys
5)Store API keys securely
6)Implement payment end point
7)Create controller to handle payment request
8)Test the payment in test mode before switching to live mode

Flutterwave's payment flow works as follows:
Make a server-side request to our create payment endpoint.
We’ll return a link to a payment page. Simply redirect your customer to this link to complete their payment.
Once the transaction is completed, we’ll redirect the customer back to your site.
web: https://developer.flutterwave.com/v3.0.0/docs/flutterwave-standard-1